# ConstructPro Mobile — Phase 2 (Calculators)

## Stack
React Native (Expo SDK 54), Expo Router (file routes), Firebase Auth, NativeWind + Tailwind, Zustand, TanStack Query, TypeScript strict.

## Rules
- No HTML/CSS/web APIs: never `document`, `window`, `localStorage`.
- TypeScript strict: no `any`; typed props; default export for route screens, named exports for components.
- Styling: NativeWind `className` on RN primitives. Prefer design tokens in `tailwind.config.js` (brand, accent, neutral). Min tap target 48px for interactive elements.
- Firebase: import auth helpers from `lib/firebase/auth.ts` in screens; use `firebase/auth` (not compat).
- Navigation: `import { router } from 'expo-router'` — `router.replace`, `router.push`, `router.back`.
- Forms (2+ fields): React Hook Form + Zod; show field errors; disable submit while submitting; no `alert()` — inline errors.
- Phase 2 scope: calculators + local history + PDF export. No Firestore, projects, site log, or payments yet.

## CURRENT PHASE UPDATE: Phase 2 — Calculators

## TOOL SCREEN PATTERN — ALL CALCULATORS FOLLOW THIS
Every tool screen has exactly:
1. ScreenHeader: back arrow, title, level badge (Basic/Mid/Advanced), optional export icon
2. ScrollView with paddingBottom: 100
3. One or more ToolInputCard sections with form fields
4. ToolResultCard — only shown after calculation, brand-100 background
5. FormulaCard — collapsible, shows formula in mono font, always at bottom
6. Sticky bottom bar (height 80, white bg, border top): Calculate button (accent-600)

## CALCULATOR RULES
- ALL formula logic in `/lib/formulas/*.ts` as pure TypeScript functions. Input type → Output type. No side effects. No React in formula files. Example: `calculateConcrete(inputs: ConcreteInputs): ConcreteResult`
- NO calculation logic inside component files.
- useMemo for expensive calculations where needed.
- Save last result + inputs to AsyncStorage key pattern `calc_history_{toolName}` via `lib/storage/calculatorHistory.ts`.

## PDF EXPORT
- Build HTML string with inline styles (no external CSS).
- Call `expo-print`'s `printToFileAsync` to get PDF URI.
- Share via `expo-sharing`'s `shareAsync`.
